snippet: As the traffic levels remained high, many state-run systems seemed to be functioning, but the federal system operating the exchanges for 34 states remained trouble-plagued.
abstract: Federal and state officials move to strengthen computer underpinnings of new online health exchanges, which proved inadequate to handle flood of consumer inquiries that began as soon as system opened and continued into the next day.

byline.original: By RICHARD PÉREZ-PEÑA, ABBY GOODNOUGH and ROBERT PEAR

lead_paragraph: As the traffic levels remained high, many state-run systems seemed to be functioning, but the federal system operating the exchanges for 34 states remained trouble-plagued.

headline.main: As Demand Stays High, Officials Try to Address Problems in Exchanges
